The body of a newborn baby boy was found at Somerset Mall in the Western Cape on Friday. CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape Social Development Department has urged parents who cannot afford to look after their children to seek assistance.The body of a newborn baby boy was found at Somerset Mall on Friday.A cleaner is believed to have discovered the infant s body in a toilet.Police have opened an inquest docket.Provincial Social Development MEC Albert Fritz says, We want to appeal to everyone and the community to please go to the nearest police station if you don t want your baby. It s the safest place to hand in your baby so that Social Services can be contacted. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)